itemDescription: aviator, one of the 'first eight' female pilots in Air Transport Auxiliary

wikipedia_page.main: Rosemary Rees MBE (23 September 1901 – 8 March 1994) was a British aviator who worked for the Air Transport Auxiliary. She was second in command to Margot Gore at Hamble from the 29th September 1941 when the site became an all-women ATA ferry pool.
